This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Natural Language Generation (NLG) tasks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the performance of different models in NLG tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it deals with the generation of high-quality text. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it discusses the use of neural networks in NLG tasks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it discusses the evaluation of models based on quality and diversity metrics.
